<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <meta name="description"
        content="Learn how to build beautiful and budget-friendly outdoor furniture using wooden pallets. From sofas to coffee tables, transform your patio with these DIY pallet projects.">
    <title>DIY Outdoor Pallet Furniture - Home Hub</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com/3.4.16"></script>
    <script>
        tailwind.config = {
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    colors: {
                        primary: "#14B8A6",
                        secondary: "#0F766E",
                    },
                    borderRadius: {
                        none: "0px",
                        sm: "4px",
                        DEFAULT: "8px",
                        md: "12px",
                        lg: "16px",
                        xl: "20px",
                        "2xl": "24px",
                        "3xl": "32px",
                        full: "9999px",
                        button: "8px",
                    },
                },
            },
        };
    </script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Pacifico&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/remixicon/4.6.0/remixicon.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/responsive.css">
</head>

<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/diy-projects" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">DIY Projects</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">Outdoor Pallet Furniture</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                How to Build Outdoor Pallet Furniture for Your Patio
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/outdoor-pallet-furniture.webp"
                                    alt="Stylish sofa made from wooden pallets on a patio"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    Wooden pallets are a treasure trove for DIY enthusiasts. They are often free or very
                                    cheap, and their sturdy construction makes them ideal for building rustic and
                                    durable outdoor furniture.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Sourcing and Preparing Pallets
                                </h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Before you start building, you need to find the right
                                    pallets and make them safe for use.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Check the Stamp:</strong> Look for the "HT" (Heat Treated) stamp. Avoid
                                        pallets marked "MB" (Methyl Bromide), which are treated with harmful chemicals.
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>Condition:</strong> Choose pallets that are in good shape without major
                                        splits or rotting wood.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Sanding:</strong> Sand the pallets thoroughly to remove splinters and
                                        smooth out rough edges.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">What Can You Build?</h2>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Sectional Sofa:</strong> Stack and secure pallets to create a layered
                                        seating area.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Coffee Table:</strong> A simple pallet on wheels makes for a great
                                        mobile outdoor table.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Vertical Garden:</strong> Use a pallet as a frame for flower pots on a
                                        small balcony.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    With some creativity and a few tools, you can turn humble wooden pallets into a
                                    beautiful outdoor oasis. Don't forget to add comfortable cushions and a
                                    weather-resistant finish!
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Safety First</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-600">Always wear gloves and eye protection when working with older
                                    pallets, as they often contain rusty nails or staples.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
            <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>